{This is a Smolen sequence: responder holds five-four in the majors with game-going values opposite a 1NT opening, and the goal is to land the strong hand in the major fit as declarer.
[BID 1N]@S @v(have|has) a balanced 15 to 17, so @v(open|opens) 1NT and @v(let|lets) partner take charge of finding the right strain.
[BID 2C]@S @v(start|starts) with Stayman, asking whether opener holds a four-card major. With five-four in the majors and enough for game, this is the first step of the Smolen route.
[BID 2D]2\D denies a four-card major. @S @v(have|has) no major to show, so @v(steer|steers) toward responder's next bid.
[BID 3S]The jump to 3\S is Smolen: it shows four spades and therefore five hearts. @S @v(point|points) opener at the five-card heart suit and asks for support.
[BID 4H]With three-card heart support, @S @v(complete|completes) the picture by bidding game in the implied five-card suit. 4\H puts the strong hand on lead from the right side.
[show NS]North's five hearts and four spades opposite South's balanced 15 found the eight-card heart fit through Smolen. Because South described the 1NT range and North jumped to show the five-three major, the partnership reached 4\H with the opening lead coming up to the strong hand.}
[Note "1:Stayman"]
[Note "2:SMOLEN"]
